00:42:56,840 --> 00:43:00,116
-|'m not ready for this. Sirius.
-You don't have a choice.

508
00:43:03,559 --> 00:43:05,868
-Someone's coming.
-Keep your friends close. Harry.

509
00:43:09,040 --> 00:43:10,917
-Who were you talking to?
-What?

510
00:43:11,079 --> 00:43:13,388
-Who says I was talking to anyone?
-I heard voices.

511
00:43:13,680 --> 00:43:17,514
Maybe you're imagining things.
Wouldn't be the first time.

512
00:43:18,040 --> 00:43:21,237
You're probably just practicing
for your next interview. I expect.

513
00:43:46,119 --> 00:43:47,677
Amazing.

514
00:43:49,560 --> 00:43:53,109
-Amazing!
-Nevi|le. You're doing it again.

515
00:43:53,640 --> 00:43:54,993
Right. sorry.

516
00:43:55,839 --> 00:43:58,717
“Magical Water Plants
of the Highland l.ochs“?

517
00:43:58,880 --> 00:44:01,917
Moody gave it to me.
That day we had tea.

518
00:44:03,360 --> 00:44:04,998
It's already been through enough people.

519
00:44:05,160 --> 00:44:07,196
Why don't you just go
and talk to him yourself?

520
00:44:08,600 --> 00:44:10,830
Ron. this is your problem. not mine.

521
00:44:10,999 --> 00:44:12,990
What do you want me to say again?

522
00:44:13,159 --> 00:44:14,433
Go.

523
00:44:17,279 --> 00:44:21,192
Ronald would like me to tell you
that Seamus told him...

524
00:44:21,799 --> 00:44:25,269
...that Dean was told by Parvati
that Hagrid's looking for you.

525
00:44:25,439 --> 00:44:27,748
Is that right? Well. you--

526
00:44:27,919 --> 00:44:28,954
What?

527
00:44:33,839 --> 00:44:36,672
-Are you sure you won't do this?
-Do it.

528
00:44:39,360 --> 00:44:42,193
Dean was told by Parvati that....

529
00:44:43,400 --> 00:44:45,516
Please don't ask me to say it again.

530
00:44:45,879 --> 00:44:47,278
Hagrid's looking for you.

531
00:44:47,760 --> 00:44:50,718
-Well. you can tell Ronald--
-|'m not an owl!

532
00:45:00,839 --> 00:45:02,989
Did you bring your father's cloak.
like I asked you?

533
00:45:03,160 --> 00:45:05,628
Yeah. I brought the cloak.
Hagrid. where are we going?

534
00:45:05,800 --> 00:45:07,153
You'll see soon enough.

535
00:45:07,320 --> 00:45:09,436
Now pay attention. this is important.

536
00:45:11,079 --> 00:45:12,432
What's with the flower?

537
00:45:13,479 --> 00:45:15,788
Hagrid. have you combed your hair?

538
00:45:16,199 --> 00:45:17,837
As a matter of fact. I have.

539
00:45:18,279 --> 00:45:21,077
You might like to try the same thing
now and again.

540
00:45:29,239 --> 00:45:30,638
Hagrid?

541
00:45:34,400 --> 00:45:36,152
The cloak! Put the cloak on!

542
00:45:42,479 --> 00:45:45,755
-Eonsoir. Olympe.
-Oh. Hagrid.

543
00:45:45,919 --> 00:45:49,468
I thought perhaps you weren't coming.
I thought perhaps...

544
00:45:49,640 --> 00:45:52,200
...you had forgotten me.

545
00:45:52,360 --> 00:45:54,237
Couldn't forget you. Olympe.

546
00:45:54,879 --> 00:45:56,551
What is it you wanted to show me?

547
00:45:58,239 --> 00:46:01,311
When we spoke earlier.
you sounded so...

548
00:46:01,640 --> 00:46:03,073
...exhilarated.

549
00:46:03,639 --> 00:46:06,358
You'll be glad you came. Trust me.

550
00:46:16,519 --> 00:46:18,191
Can we get closer?

551
00:46:25,680 --> 00:46:27,079
Dragons?

552
00:46:27,239 --> 00:46:28,672
That's the first task?

553
00:46:29,079 --> 00:46:30,956
-You're joking.
-Come on. Harry.

554
00:46:32,239 --> 00:46:35,151
These are seriously
misunderstood creatures.

555
00:46:36,199 --> 00:46:37,632
Oh. crikey!

556
00:46:38,160 --> 00:46:40,151
Although. I have to admit...

557
00:46:40,320 --> 00:46:43,039
...that Horntail is a right nasty
piece of work.

558
00:46:43,199 --> 00:46:45,838
Poor Ron nearly fainted
just seeing him. you know.

559
00:46:47,359 --> 00:46:49,315
-Ron was here?
-Oh. sure.

560
00:46:49,479 --> 00:46:52,835
His brother Charlie helped
to bring him over from Romania.

561
00:46:52,999 --> 00:46:54,318
Didn't Ron tell you that?

562
00:46:56,239 --> 00:46:57,592
No. he didn't.

563
00:46:58,280 --> 00:47:00,077
He didn't tell me a thing.

564
00:47:09,639 --> 00:47:12,597
-You cheat. Potter.
-You stink. Potter.

565
00:47:14,039 --> 00:47:16,599
-Good luck. Potter.
-Potter stinks!

566
00:47:16,759 --> 00:47:19,319
-Cedric rules.
-Thanks.

567
00:47:20,359 --> 00:47:21,951
Like the badge?

568
00:47:22,479 --> 00:47:24,151
Excuse me.

569
00:47:28,159 --> 00:47:29,558
Harry.

570
00:47:30,120 --> 00:47:31,997
Hey! Read the badge. Potter!

571
00:47:32,160 --> 00:47:33,593
Can I have a word?

572
00:47:34,519 --> 00:47:36,316
-All right.
-You stink. Potter!

573
00:47:36,479 --> 00:47:39,357
-Potter. you stink!
-Harry Potter smells!

574
00:47:41,760 --> 00:47:44,194
Dragons. That's the first task.

575
00:47:44,359 --> 00:47:47,396
-They've got one for each of us.
-Come on. Ced!

576
00:47:47,560 --> 00:47:49,471
Are you serious?

577
00:47:50,239 --> 00:47:53,151
And Fleur and Krum. do they--?

578
00:47:53,319 --> 00:47:55,469
-Yes.
-Come on. Ced. leave him.

579
00:47:55,640 --> 00:47:57,039
-Right.
-He's not worth it.

580
00:47:57,199 --> 00:47:59,588
-Read the badges. Potter!
-Hey. listen. About the badges.

581
00:47:59,760 --> 00:48:02,672
-|'ve asked them not to wear them. but--
-Don't worry about it.

582
00:48:02,840 --> 00:48:05,149
It's not like I try
to blow things up. exactly.

583
00:48:05,840 --> 00:48:07,239
It just happens a fair bit.

584
00:48:07,400 --> 00:48:10,358
You have to admit. though.
fire's pretty fascinating.

585
00:48:10,519 --> 00:48:12,316
You're a right foul git. you know that?

586
00:48:12,479 --> 00:48:14,595
-You think so?
-I know so.

587
00:48:14,760 --> 00:48:16,034
Anything else?

588
00:48:16,199 --> 00:48:19,555
-Yeah. Stay away from me.
-Fine.

589
00:48:21,839 --> 00:48:25,309
-There's Potter. Cheat.
-Why so tense. Potter?

590
00:48:26,039 --> 00:48:28,348
My father and l have a bet. you see.

591
00:48:28,519 --> 00:48:31,556
I don't think you're gonna last
10 minutes in this tournament.

592
00:48:34,039 --> 00:48:36,837
He disagrees.
He thinks you won't last five.

593
00:48:36,999 --> 00:48:39,991
ldon't give a damn
what your father thinks. Malfoy.

594
00:48:40,959 --> 00:48:44,793
He's vile and cruel.
And you're just pathetic.

595
00:48:45,680 --> 00:48:48,069
-Pathetic?
-Oh. no. you don't. sonny!

596
00:48:50,239 --> 00:48:52,992
l'll teach you to curse someone
when their back is turned!

597
00:48:53,160 --> 00:48:56,835
You stinking. cowardly. scummy...

598
00:48:57,000 --> 00:48:58,672
-Professor Moody!
-...back-shooting--

599
00:48:58,839 --> 00:49:01,637
-What are you doing?
-Teaching.

600
00:49:02,600 --> 00:49:06,593
-|s that a--? Is that a student?
-Technical|y. it's a ferret.

601
00:49:12,039 --> 00:49:13,836
Stand still! Stand still!

602
00:49:24,360 --> 00:49:26,476
-My father will hear about this!
-|s that a threat?

603
00:49:26,640 --> 00:49:28,517
-Professor Moody!
-|s that a threat?

604
00:49:28,680 --> 00:49:30,432
Professor!

605
00:49:30,600 --> 00:49:34,036
I could tell you stories about your father
that would curl even your greasy hair!

606
00:49:34,199 --> 00:49:36,793
-A|astor! Alastor.
-It doesn't end here!

607
00:49:36,959 --> 00:49:40,588
We never use transfiguration
as a punishment!

608
00:49:40,759 --> 00:49:42,875
Surely Dumbledore told you that.

609
00:49:43,399 --> 00:49:47,677
-He might've mentioned it.
-Well. you will do well to remember it.

610
00:49:48,720 --> 00:49:50,119
Away!

611
00:49:53,119 --> 00:49:55,235
You. Come with me.

612
00:50:28,999 --> 00:50:30,990
That's a Foe-Glass.

613
00:50:31,719 --> 00:50:33,710
Lets me keep an eye on my enemies.

614
00:50:34,159 --> 00:50:38,391
If I can see the whites of their eyes.
they're standing right behind me.

615
00:50:42,400 --> 00:50:44,755
Wouldn't even bother telling you
what's in there.

616
00:50:44,919 --> 00:50:46,875
You wouldn't believe it if I did.

617
00:50:47,119 --> 00:50:48,757
Now...

618
00:50:50,359 --> 00:50:53,078
...what are you going to do
about your dragon?

619
00:50:56,839 --> 00:50:59,034
Well. you know. ljust thought l'd....

620
00:51:00,439 --> 00:51:01,872
Sit.

621
00:51:05,439 --> 00:51:06,758
Listen to me. Potter.

622
00:51:07,719 --> 00:51:08,834
Your pal Diggory?

623
00:51:09,000 --> 00:51:13,232
By your age. he could turn a whistle into
a watch and have it sing you the time.

624
00:51:14,400 --> 00:51:15,594
Miss Delacour?

625
00:51:15,999 --> 00:51:18,593
She's as much a fairy princess as I am.

626
00:51:19,079 --> 00:51:22,515
As for Krum. his head
may be filled with sawdust...

627
00:51:22,680 --> 00:51:24,750
...but Karkaroff's is not.

628
00:51:24,919 --> 00:51:26,671
They'll have a strategy.

629
00:51:26,839 --> 00:51:30,149
And you can bet that it will
play to Krum's strengths.

630
00:51:34,800 --> 00:51:36,313
Come on. Potter.

631
00:51:36,479 --> 00:51:38,470
What are your strengths?

632
00:51:39,999 --> 00:51:41,318
I don't know.

633
00:51:41,479 --> 00:51:44,152
Well. I can fly.
lmean. I'm a fair flyer. But l....

634
00:51:44,320 --> 00:51:48,199
-Better than fair. the way I heard it.
-But I'm not allowed a broom.

635
00:51:48,359 --> 00:51:51,829
You're allowed a wand.

636
00:51:58,000 --> 00:51:59,399
Bets! Place your bets!

637
00:51:59,559 --> 00:52:01,629
Bets taken! Bets taken here!

638
00:52:01,799 --> 00:52:04,632
Step up. folks! Who fancies a flutter
in today's bloodbath?

639
00:52:04,800 --> 00:52:07,473
Smart money's on Krum to survive!
Any bets?

640
00:52:07,719 --> 00:52:09,152
Yes. sir?

641
00:52:09,480 --> 00:52:12,040
Ten-to-1 for Fleur. There you go.
Thank you very much.

642
00:52:12,560 --> 00:52:14,437
Your attention, please.

643
00:52:14,640 --> 00:52:17,154
This is a great day for all of us.

644
00:52:20,440 --> 00:52:24,513
Each of the three tasks involves
very considerable danger.

645
00:52:24,679 --> 00:52:27,239
Please keep your seats at all times.

646
00:52:27,399 --> 00:52:30,038
This will minimize any risks
you may be exposed to.

647
00:52:30,199 --> 00:52:33,475
-Harry? Is that you?
-Yeah.

648
00:52:33,640 --> 00:52:35,278
I'm sure we all wish our champions...

649
00:52:35,439 --> 00:52:38,397
-How are you feeling? Okay?
-...the greatest of luck.

650
00:52:40,599 --> 00:52:43,875
The key is to concentrate.
After that. you just have to--

651
00:52:44,039 --> 00:52:45,791
Battle a dragon.

652
00:52:49,920 --> 00:52:52,275
Young love.

653
00:52:53,000 --> 00:52:54,194
How...

654
00:52:56,560 --> 00:52:57,788
...stirring.

655
00:53:00,359 --> 00:53:03,396
If everything goes unfortunately today...

656
00:53:03,560 --> 00:53:06,233
...you two may even
make the front page.

657
00:53:06,400 --> 00:53:08,516
You have no business here.

658
00:53:08,680 --> 00:53:10,591
This tent is for champions...

659
00:53:10,960 --> 00:53:12,598
...and friends.

660
00:53:15,280 --> 00:53:19,273
No matter. We've got what we wanted.

661
00:53:22,279 --> 00:53:24,998
Good day. champions.
Gather round. please.

662
00:53:25,160 --> 00:53:29,153
Now. you've waited. you've wondered.
and at last the moment has arrived.

663
00:53:29,320 --> 00:53:32,437
A moment only four of you
can fully appreciate.

664
00:53:32,599 --> 00:53:34,635
What are you doing here. Miss Granger?

665
00:53:35,879 --> 00:53:37,471
Sorry. I'll just go.

666
00:53:37,639 --> 00:53:39,118
Barty. the bag.

667
00:53:39,560 --> 00:53:41,676
Champions. in a circle around me.

668
00:53:41,839 --> 00:53:44,831
Miss Delacour. over here. Mr. Krum.

669
00:53:45,000 --> 00:53:48,754
And. Potter. Mr. Potter. over here.
That's right. Now...

670
00:53:48,919 --> 00:53:51,228
...Miss Delacour. if you will.

671
00:53:55,160 --> 00:53:56,752
The Welsh Green.

672
00:54:01,200 --> 00:54:02,428
Mr. Krum.

673
00:54:05,319 --> 00:54:07,150
The Chinese Fireball.

674
00:54:13,360 --> 00:54:15,669
The Swedish Short-Snout.

675
00:54:16,119 --> 00:54:18,030
-Which leaves....
-The Horntail.

676
00:54:18,199 --> 00:54:20,349
-What's that. boy?
-Nothing.

677
00:54:23,639 --> 00:54:25,948
The Hungarian Horntail.

678
00:54:28,039 --> 00:54:31,031
These represent four
very real dragons...

679
00:54:31,200 --> 00:54:34,112
...each of which has been given
a golden egg to protect.

680
00:54:34,279 --> 00:54:36,668
Your objective is simple:

681
00:54:36,839 --> 00:54:38,272
Collect the egg.

682
00:54:38,440 --> 00:54:41,318
This you must do.
for each egg contains a clue...

683
00:54:41,479 --> 00:54:44,835
...without which you cannot hope
to proceed to the next task.

684
00:54:45,000 --> 00:54:46,274
Any questions?

685
00:54:47,240 --> 00:54:49,800
Very well. Good luck. champions.

686
00:54:49,959 --> 00:54:52,632
Mr. Diggory. at the sound of the cannon.
you may--

687
00:55:00,959 --> 00:55:04,634
Diggory! Diggory! Diggory!

688
00:55:15,720 --> 00:55:18,951
Three of our champions
have now faced their dragons...

689
00:55:19,120 --> 00:55:22,476
...and so each one of them
will proceed to the next task.

690
00:55:23,040 --> 00:55:25,998
And now our fourth
and final contestant.

691
00:55:27,880 --> 00:55:31,316
Harry! Harry! Harry!

692
00:56:35,680 --> 00:56:38,478
Your wand. Harry! Your wand!

693
00:56:38,960 --> 00:56:40,916
A ccio Firebolt!

694
00:57:08,720 --> 00:57:10,790
-Yeah!
-Yes!

695
00:57:19,360 --> 00:57:20,713
Oh. my God.

696
00:57:29,960 --> 00:57:33,111
-Yeah!
-Yeah! Well done. dragon!

697
00:59:58,920 --> 01:00:00,990
Yes! Yes!

698
01:00:23,240 --> 01:00:25,834
-Yes. Harry!
-Knew you wouldn't die. Lose a leg.

699
01:00:25,999 --> 01:00:27,876
-Or an arm.
-Pack it in altogether?

700
01:00:28,039 --> 01:00:29,711
-Never!
-Never!

701
01:00:31,719 --> 01:00:32,993
Shush!

702
01:00:33,480 --> 01:00:36,040
Go on. Harry. What's the clue?

703
01:00:36,999 --> 01:00:39,718
-Who wants me to open it?
-Yes!

704
01:00:40,519 --> 01:00:42,908
-Do you want me to open it?
-Yes!

705
01:00:53,639 --> 01:00:55,948
What the bloody hell was that?

706
01:00:59,920 --> 01:01:02,559
All right. everyone!
Go back to your knitting.

707
01:01:02,720 --> 01:01:06,599
This is gonna be uncomfortable enough
without all you nosy sods listening in.

708
01:01:09,640 --> 01:01:13,394
I reckon you have to be barking mad to
put your own name in the Goblet of Fire.

709
01:01:13,799 --> 01:01:16,393
Caught on. have you?
Took you long enough.

710
01:01:17,479 --> 01:01:19,515
I wasn't the only one
who thought you'd done it.

711
01:01:19,680 --> 01:01:21,830
Everyone was saying it
behind your back.

712
01:01:23,960 --> 01:01:27,077
Brilliant.
That makes me feel loads better.

713
01:01:27,960 --> 01:01:31,191
-Least I warned you about the dragons.
-Hagrid warned me about the dragons.

714
01:01:31,360 --> 01:01:32,793
No. no. no. I did.

715
01:01:32,960 --> 01:01:35,872
No. don't you remember?
I told Hermione to tell you...

716
01:01:36,039 --> 01:01:39,918
...that Seamus told me that Parvati
told Dean that Hagrid was looking for you.

717
01:01:40,080 --> 01:01:43,868
Seamus never actually told me anything.
so it was really me all along.

718
01:01:44,839 --> 01:01:47,717
I thought we'd be all right. you know...

719
01:01:47,920 --> 01:01:49,831
...after you'd figured that out.

720
01:01:50,199 --> 01:01:52,759
Who--? Who could possibly
figure that out?

721
01:01:53,399 --> 01:01:54,752
That's completely mental.

722
01:01:54,919 --> 01:01:57,831
Yeah. Isn't it?

723
01:01:58,000 --> 01:01:59,956
I suppose I was a bit distraught.

724
01:02:02,440 --> 01:02:04,078
Boys.

725
01:02:27,560 --> 01:02:28,913
-Hi. Harry.
-Hi. Harry.

726
01:02:32,400 --> 01:02:34,914
Cho. Harry's looking at you.

727
01:02:38,680 --> 01:02:40,318
Shush.

728
01:02:41,000 --> 01:02:42,274
Look at this!

729
01:02:44,199 --> 01:02:46,588
I can't believe it! She's done it again.

730
01:02:47,599 --> 01:02:49,749
“Miss Granger.
a plain but ambitious girl...

731
01:02:49,920 --> 01:02:52,559
...seems to be developing a taste
for famous wizards.

732
01:02:52,720 --> 01:02:54,915
Her latest prey. sources report...

733
01:02:55,079 --> 01:02:58,549
...is none other than the
Bulgarian bonbon. Viktor Krum.

734
01:02:58,840 --> 01:03:02,594
No word yet on how Harry Potter's
taking this latest emotional blow.“

735
01:03:03,920 --> 01:03:05,797
Parcel for you. Mr. Weasley.

736
01:03:05,960 --> 01:03:07,393
Thank you. Nigel.

737
01:03:12,000 --> 01:03:14,719
Not now. Nigel. Later.

738
01:03:16,479 --> 01:03:17,958
Go on.

739
01:03:23,080 --> 01:03:25,719
I told him I'd get him Harry's autograph.

740
01:03:27,840 --> 01:03:29,512
Oh. look. Mum's sent me something.

741
01:03:37,319 --> 01:03:39,071
Mum sent me a dress.

742
01:03:39,240 --> 01:03:42,915
Well. it does match your eyes.
Is there a bonnet?

743
01:03:43,360 --> 01:03:45,112
Nose down. Harry.

744
01:03:45,640 --> 01:03:49,349
-Ginny. these must be for you.
-|'m not wearing that. it's ghastly.

745
01:03:51,079 --> 01:03:52,831
What are you on about?

746
01:03:53,000 --> 01:03:54,877
They're not for Ginny.

747
01:03:55,039 --> 01:03:56,313
They're for you.

748
01:03:57,319 --> 01:04:00,914
-Dress robes.
-Dress robes? For what?

749
01:04:02,119 --> 01:04:04,189
The Yule Ball...

750
01:04:04,359 --> 01:04:09,479
...has been a tradition
of the Triwizard Tournament...

751
01:04:10,160 --> 01:04:12,151
...since its inception.

752
01:04:12,799 --> 01:04:16,508
On Christmas Eve night.
we and our guests...

