01:25:25,799 --> 01:25:28,233
“An hour long you'll have to look.“

1003
01:25:28,399 --> 01:25:31,709
Again. obvious. Though. admittedly.
potentially problematic.

1004
01:25:33,040 --> 01:25:34,837
“Potentially problematic“?

1005
01:25:34,999 --> 01:25:38,116
When's the last time you held your breath
underwater for an hour. Hermione?

1006
01:25:38,640 --> 01:25:42,792
Look. Harry. we can do this.
The three of us can figure it out.

1007
01:25:42,959 --> 01:25:45,348
Hate to break up the skull session.

1008
01:25:45,519 --> 01:25:47,430
Professor McGonagall
wants you in her office.

1009
01:25:47,680 --> 01:25:49,955
Not you. Potter.
just Weasley and Granger.

1010
01:25:50,119 --> 01:25:52,679
But. sir. the second task
is only hours away. and--

1011
01:25:52,839 --> 01:25:55,353
Exactly. Presumably Potter
is well prepared by now...

1012
01:25:55,519 --> 01:25:57,316
...and could do with
a good night's sleep.

1013
01:25:57,479 --> 01:25:59,868
Go. Now!

1014
01:26:09,440 --> 01:26:11,158
Longbottom!

1015
01:26:11,320 --> 01:26:13,231
Why don't you help Potter
put his books back.

1016
01:26:21,559 --> 01:26:23,675
You know.
if you're interested in plants...

1017
01:26:23,840 --> 01:26:26,308
...you'd be better off with
Goshawk's Guide to Herbology.

1018
01:26:26,920 --> 01:26:31,038
Do you know there's a wizard in Nepal
who's growing gravity-resistant trees?

1019
01:26:31,200 --> 01:26:34,795
Neville. no offense.
but I really don't care...

1020
01:26:35,399 --> 01:26:37,037
...about plants.

1021
01:26:37,360 --> 01:26:38,998
Now. if there's...

1022
01:26:39,160 --> 01:26:43,756
...a Tibetan turnip that will allow me
to breathe underwater for an hour...

1023
01:26:43,919 --> 01:26:46,308
...then great. But otherwise--

1024
01:26:46,480 --> 01:26:50,109
I don't know about a turnip.
But you could always use gillyweed.

1025
01:26:51,320 --> 01:26:54,039
-Any bets? Any bets?
-Come on. place your bets!

1026
01:26:54,200 --> 01:26:55,599
Step up. mates! Don't be shy.

1027
01:26:55,760 --> 01:26:57,159
-Three lads.
-One lady.

1028
01:26:57,320 --> 01:26:59,390
-Four go down.
-But do four come up?

1029
01:26:59,560 --> 01:27:00,993
Don't be so mean.

1030
01:27:01,599 --> 01:27:03,317
-Any bets?
-F|eur's 10-1.

1031
01:27:05,440 --> 01:27:07,351
-You're sure about this. Neville?
-Abso|ute|y.

1032
01:27:07,519 --> 01:27:09,350
-For an hour?
-Most likely.

1033
01:27:09,519 --> 01:27:10,952
Most likely?

1034
01:27:11,120 --> 01:27:13,236
Well. there is some debate
among herbologists...

1035
01:27:13,399 --> 01:27:15,754
...as to the effects of fresh water
versus salt water--

1036
01:27:15,919 --> 01:27:18,479
You're telling me this now?
You must be joking!

1037
01:27:18,640 --> 01:27:20,517
| just wanted to help.

1038
01:27:20,679 --> 01:27:23,671
Well. that makes you a right sight
better than Ron and Hermione.

1039
01:27:23,839 --> 01:27:25,511
Where are they anyway?

1040
01:27:25,680 --> 01:27:28,592
-You seem a little tense. Harry.
-Do I?

1041
01:27:35,320 --> 01:27:37,470
Welcome to the second task.

1042
01:27:37,640 --> 01:27:41,155
Last night, something was stolen
from each of our champions.

1043
01:27:41,320 --> 01:27:42,639
A treasure of sorts.

1044
01:27:42,799 --> 01:27:45,313
These four treasures,
one for each champion...

1045
01:27:45,480 --> 01:27:48,074
...now lie on the bottom
of the Black Lake.

1046
01:27:48,240 --> 01:27:49,753
In order to win...

1047
01:27:49,920 --> 01:27:53,595
...each champion need only find
their treasure and return to the surface.

1048
01:27:53,760 --> 01:27:56,274
-Simple enough, except for this:
-Put that in your mouth.

1049
01:27:56,440 --> 01:27:59,910
They will have but one hour to do so,
and one hour only.

1050
01:28:00,079 --> 01:28:03,788
After that, they'll be on their own.
No magic will save them.

1051
01:28:04,320 --> 01:28:06,470
You may begin
at the sound of the cannon.

1052
01:28:31,919 --> 01:28:34,752
-What's the matter with him?
-I don't know. I can't see him.

1053
01:28:36,039 --> 01:28:38,837
Oh. my God.
l've killed Harry Potter.

1054
01:28:40,680 --> 01:28:42,477
Yeah!

1055
01:28:43,599 --> 01:28:45,157
What?

1056
01:30:01,479 --> 01:30:03,549
The Beauxbatons champion,
Miss Delacour...

1057
01:30:03,719 --> 01:30:06,108
...has unfortunately
been forced to retire...

1058
01:30:06,760 --> 01:30:09,718
...so she will take no further part
in this task.

1059
01:31:24,320 --> 01:31:26,038
But she's my friend too!

1060
01:31:27,600 --> 01:31:29,272
Only one!

1061
01:32:18,519 --> 01:32:20,316
Let's get down below.

1062
01:32:29,960 --> 01:32:32,679
Krum! Krum! Krum!

1063
01:33:27,800 --> 01:33:29,472
Yes!

1064
01:33:46,839 --> 01:33:48,830
Ascendio!

1065
01:33:53,840 --> 01:33:55,478
Harry!

1066
01:33:57,680 --> 01:33:59,079
He's all right.

1067
01:34:00,239 --> 01:34:01,638
He's all right. Barty!

1068
01:34:01,799 --> 01:34:05,075
-Go get him another towel.
-I want all the judges over here now!

1069
01:34:05,639 --> 01:34:08,949
You saved her. even though
she wasn't yours to save.

1070
01:34:09,639 --> 01:34:11,197
My little sister.

1071
01:34:11,639 --> 01:34:13,152
Thank you.

1072
01:34:13,919 --> 01:34:16,513
And you! You helped.

1073
01:34:17,159 --> 01:34:20,037
Well. yeah. a bit.

1074
01:34:26,960 --> 01:34:28,075
-Harry!
-Hermione!

1075
01:34:28,239 --> 01:34:30,799
Are you all right? You must be freezing.

1076
01:34:31,999 --> 01:34:33,830
Personally. I think
you behaved admirably.

1077
01:34:33,999 --> 01:34:35,955
I finished last. Hermione.

1078
01:34:36,760 --> 01:34:40,719
Next to last.
Fleur never got past the Grindylows.

1079
01:34:40,879 --> 01:34:43,996
Krum! Krum! Krum!

1080
01:34:44,159 --> 01:34:46,912
-Come on! Come on!
-Attention!

1081
01:34:49,160 --> 01:34:51,674
Attention!

1082
01:34:52,119 --> 01:34:55,828
The winner is Mr. Diggory...

1083
01:34:56,239 --> 01:34:59,595
...who showed innate command
of the Bubble-Head Charm.

1084
01:34:59,759 --> 01:35:02,319
However. seeing as Mr. Potter
would have finished first...

1085
01:35:02,480 --> 01:35:07,235
...had it not been for his determination
to rescue not only Mr. Weasley...

1086
01:35:07,399 --> 01:35:11,517
...but the others as well.
we've agreed to award him...

1087
01:35:11,679 --> 01:35:13,590
...second place...

1088
01:35:13,759 --> 01:35:15,158
-Second place!
-Well done!

1089
01:35:15,320 --> 01:35:17,880
...for outstanding moral fiber!

1090
01:35:19,080 --> 01:35:20,559
Yes!

1091
01:35:23,919 --> 01:35:25,637
-Right on.
-All that moral fiber. eh?

1092
01:35:25,800 --> 01:35:27,392
-|t's great.
-Mora| fiber?

1093
01:35:27,559 --> 01:35:29,789
Blimey. Even when you go wrong.
it turns out right.

1094
01:35:29,959 --> 01:35:32,519
-Yeah. well done. Moral Fiber.
-Congratu|ations. Potter.

1095
01:35:32,679 --> 01:35:34,271
-A fine achievement.
-Thank you.

1096
01:35:34,440 --> 01:35:35,919
Well done. boy.

1097
01:35:36,079 --> 01:35:39,196
-See you at Hagrid's. Harry.
-|'m sorry we haven't spoken.

1098
01:35:39,360 --> 01:35:43,194
After all. your story is one
I've heard so many times.

1099
01:35:44,160 --> 01:35:47,470
Ouite remarkable. really.
Tragic. of course...

1100
01:35:47,640 --> 01:35:49,517
...to lose one's family.

1101
01:35:51,480 --> 01:35:53,550
Never whole again. are we?

1102
01:35:55,720 --> 01:35:57,676
Still. life goes on...

1103
01:35:58,360 --> 01:35:59,952
...and here we stand.

1104
01:36:02,759 --> 01:36:05,319
I'm sure your parents would be
very proud of you today. Potter.

1105
01:36:05,480 --> 01:36:06,913
Bartemius!

1106
01:36:07,080 --> 01:36:11,039
Not trying to lure Potter into one of the
Ministry's summer internships. are we?

1107
01:36:11,200 --> 01:36:14,476
The last boy who went into the
Department of Mysteries never came out!

1108
01:36:26,239 --> 01:36:28,036
And they say I'm mad.

1109
01:36:36,960 --> 01:36:40,509
Now. I remember--
I remember when | first met you all.

1110
01:36:40,680 --> 01:36:43,558
Biggest bunch of misfits
I ever set eyes on.

1111
01:36:44,080 --> 01:36:46,548
Suppose you remind me
of meself a little.

1112
01:36:46,720 --> 01:36:50,599
-And here we all are. four years later.
-We're still a bunch of misfits.

1113
01:36:50,759 --> 01:36:53,956
Well. maybe.
but we've all got each other.

1114
01:36:54,119 --> 01:36:55,598
And Harry. of course.

1115
01:36:55,759 --> 01:37:00,913
Soon to be the youngest
Triwizard champion there's ever been!

1116
01:37:01,119 --> 01:37:03,075
Hooray!

1117
01:37:04,440 --> 01:37:06,829
Hogwarts, Hogwarts
Hoggy Warty Hogwarts

1118
01:37:06,999 --> 01:37:09,513
Teach us something, please

1119
01:37:19,080 --> 01:37:20,513
Mr. Crouch?

1120
01:37:27,320 --> 01:37:30,756
A man has died here. Fudge. And he
won't be the last. You must take action.

1121
01:37:30,920 --> 01:37:32,433
I will not.

1122
01:37:32,600 --> 01:37:36,513
In times like these. the wizard world looks
to its leaders for strength. Dumbledore!

1123
01:37:36,679 --> 01:37:37,998
Then for once show them some!

1124
01:37:38,160 --> 01:37:42,039
The Triwizard Tournament will not be
canceled. I will not be seen as a coward!

1125
01:37:42,199 --> 01:37:45,271
A true leader does what is right.
no matter what others think.

1126
01:37:45,439 --> 01:37:48,112
-What did you say to me?
-Excuse me. gentlemen.

1127
01:37:48,279 --> 01:37:51,794
It may interest you to know
this conversation is no longer private.

1128
01:37:55,960 --> 01:37:57,473
Oh. Harry!

1129
01:37:57,639 --> 01:37:59,834
Harry. how good to see you again.

1130
01:38:00,639 --> 01:38:02,072
I can come back later. professor.

1131
01:38:02,239 --> 01:38:05,470
Not necessary. Harry. The minister and l
are done. I'll be back in a moment.

1132
01:38:05,640 --> 01:38:08,074
Minister. after you.

1133
01:38:08,600 --> 01:38:10,511
There you are. Your hat.

1134
01:38:10,680 --> 01:38:14,195
Oh. Harry. do feel free to indulge in
a little Licorice Snap in my absence.

1135
01:38:14,360 --> 01:38:17,397
But I have to warn you.
they're a wee bit sharp.

1136
01:39:45,160 --> 01:39:46,673
Professor?

1137
01:39:46,840 --> 01:39:49,274
-Professor.
-Yeah.

1138
01:39:59,720 --> 01:40:03,349
lgor Karkaroff. you have been brought
from Azkaban at your own request...

1139
01:40:03,519 --> 01:40:05,350
...to present evidence to this council.

1140
01:40:05,519 --> 01:40:08,113
Should your testimony
prove consequential...

1141
01:40:08,279 --> 01:40:12,192
...council may be prepared
to order your immediate release.

1142
01:40:12,359 --> 01:40:16,750
Until such time. you remain in the eyes
of the Ministry a convicted Death Eater.

1143
01:40:16,919 --> 01:40:18,477
Do you accept these terms?

1144
01:40:19,079 --> 01:40:21,639
-I do. sir.
-And what do you wish to present?

1145
01:40:21,999 --> 01:40:24,354
l have names. sir.

1146
01:40:24,879 --> 01:40:28,349
There was Rosier. Evan Rosier.

1147
01:40:30,919 --> 01:40:33,308
-Rosier is dead.
-He took a piece of me with him...

1148
01:40:33,479 --> 01:40:35,515
-...though. didn't he?
-I didn't know.

1149
01:40:35,720 --> 01:40:38,234
-If that is all the witness has to offer--
-No. no. no.

1150
01:40:38,399 --> 01:40:41,550
There was Rookwood! He was a spy.

1151
01:40:41,720 --> 01:40:43,995
Augustus Rookwood?
Of the Department of Mysteries?

1152
01:40:44,160 --> 01:40:45,275
Yeah. the same.

1153
01:40:45,439 --> 01:40:48,988
He passed information to You-Know-Who
from inside the Ministry itself.

1154
01:40:50,160 --> 01:40:53,311
Very well. Council will deliberate.

1155
01:40:53,480 --> 01:40:55,357
In the meantime.
you will return to Azkaban.

1156
01:40:55,519 --> 01:41:00,035
No! Wait. please! Please. I have more!
What about Snape? Severus Snape?

1157
01:41:00,200 --> 01:41:03,078
As the council is aware.
I've given evidence on this matter.

1158
01:41:03,239 --> 01:41:07,027
Severus Snape was indeed a Death Eater
and. prior to Lord Voldemort's downfall...

1159
01:41:07,199 --> 01:41:10,077
-...turned spy for us at great personal risk.
-|t's a lie!

1160
01:41:10,239 --> 01:41:13,549
-Today he's no more a Death Eater than I.
-Snape remains faithful to the Dark Lord!

1161
01:41:13,720 --> 01:41:15,870
Silence!

1162
01:41:16,480 --> 01:41:19,756
Unless the witness possesses
any genuine name of consequence...

1163
01:41:19,919 --> 01:41:21,955
...this session is now concluded.

1164
01:41:22,119 --> 01:41:24,075
Oh. no, no, no.

1165
01:41:24,999 --> 01:41:26,432
I've heard about one more.

1166
01:41:26,600 --> 01:41:29,034
-What's that?
-The name.

1167
01:41:29,200 --> 01:41:30,599
-Yes?
-I know for a fact...

1168
01:41:30,759 --> 01:41:32,715
...this person took part
in the capture...

1169
01:41:32,879 --> 01:41:34,949
...and. by means
of the Cruciatus Curse...

1170
01:41:35,119 --> 01:41:38,475
...torture of the Auror Frank Longbottom
and his wife!

1171
01:41:38,639 --> 01:41:40,869
The name.
Give me the wretched name!

1172
01:41:41,039 --> 01:41:43,473
Barty Crouch...

1173
01:41:46,079 --> 01:41:47,068
...Junior.

1174
01:41:56,160 --> 01:41:57,798
Hold him down!

1175
01:42:01,279 --> 01:42:04,749
Get your filthy hands off me.
you pathetic little men!

1176
01:42:06,399 --> 01:42:07,912
Hello. Father.

1177
01:42:09,280 --> 01:42:11,236
You are no son of mine.

1178
01:42:22,119 --> 01:42:26,397
Curiosity is not a sin. Harry.
But you should exercise caution.

1179
01:42:27,719 --> 01:42:29,038
It's a Pensieve.

1180
01:42:29,200 --> 01:42:33,671
Very useful if. like me.
you find your mind a wee bit stretched.

1181
01:42:33,839 --> 01:42:37,229
It allows me to see once more
things I've already seen.

1182
01:42:37,679 --> 01:42:40,512
You see. Harry. I have searched
and searched for something...

1183
01:42:40,679 --> 01:42:42,192
...some small detail...

1184
01:42:43,560 --> 01:42:45,596
...something I might have overlooked...

1185
01:42:45,759 --> 01:42:49,798
...something that would explain why
these terrible things have happened.

1186
01:42:50,560 --> 01:42:54,269
Every time | get close to an answer.
it slips away.

1187
01:42:55,279 --> 01:42:56,837
lt's maddening.

1188
01:42:59,119 --> 01:43:00,757
Sir? Mr. Crouch's son.

1189
01:43:01,479 --> 01:43:03,470
What exactly happened to him?

1190
01:43:03,639 --> 01:43:08,235
He was sent to Azkaban.
Destroyed Barty to do it.

1191
01:43:08,879 --> 01:43:12,349
But he had no choice.
The evidence was overwhelming.

1192
01:43:13,759 --> 01:43:16,592
-Why do you ask?
-|t's just that l....

1193
01:43:17,319 --> 01:43:19,355
I had a dream about him.

1194
01:43:21,519 --> 01:43:24,192
It was in the summer. before school.

1195
01:43:26,279 --> 01:43:29,157
In the dream, I was in a house.

1196
01:43:29,319 --> 01:43:33,915
And Voldemort was there,
only he wasn 't quite human.

1197
01:43:34,080 --> 01:43:37,550
And Wormtail was there too.
And Mr. Crouch 's son.

1198
01:43:37,919 --> 01:43:40,638
-Have there been others like this dream?
-Yes.

1199
01:43:41,439 --> 01:43:42,997
Always the same one.

1200
01:43:45,920 --> 01:43:48,150
Sir. these dreams...

1201
01:43:48,320 --> 01:43:53,314
...what I see. you don't think
it's actually happening. do you?

1202
01:43:54,840 --> 01:43:57,718
I think it's unwise for you
to linger over these dreams. Harry.

1203
01:43:58,200 --> 01:44:00,077
I think it's best if you simply...

1204
01:44:05,480 --> 01:44:07,198
...cast them away.

1205
01:44:16,080 --> 01:44:19,868
It's a sign. Severus.
You know what it means as well as l.

1206
01:44:28,239 --> 01:44:29,388
Potter!

1207
01:44:29,560 --> 01:44:31,994
What's your hurry?

1208
01:44:36,879 --> 01:44:40,508
Congratulations. your performance
in the Black Lake was inspiring.

1209
01:44:40,679 --> 01:44:42,829
Gillyweed. am I correct?

1210
01:44:43,559 --> 01:44:45,038
Yes. sir.

1211
01:44:45,960 --> 01:44:47,279
Ingenious.

1212
01:44:49,040 --> 01:44:52,828
A rather rare herb. gillyweed.

1213
01:44:53,639 --> 01:44:56,995
Not something found
in your everyday garden.

1214
01:44:58,599 --> 01:45:00,476
Nor is this.

1215
01:45:04,519 --> 01:45:06,111
Know what it is?

1216
01:45:07,360 --> 01:45:08,713
Bubble juice. sir?

1217
01:45:09,279 --> 01:45:11,076
Veritaserum.

1218
01:45:11,799 --> 01:45:15,348
Three drops of this and You-Know-Who
himself would spill his darkest secrets.

1219
01:45:15,519 --> 01:45:20,468
The use of it on a student is.
regrettably. forbidden. However...

1220
01:45:21,119 --> 01:45:24,031
...should you ever steal
from my personal stores again...

1221
01:45:24,200 --> 01:45:28,830
...my hand might just slip over
your morning pumpkin juice.

1222
01:45:28,999 --> 01:45:33,231
-I haven't stolen anything.
-Don't lie to me.

1223
01:45:34,319 --> 01:45:39,791
Gillyweed may be innocuous.
but boomslang skin. lacewing flies?

1224
01:45:40,479 --> 01:45:43,676
You and your little friends are brewing
Polyjuice Potion. and believe me...

1225
01:45:43,839 --> 01:45:45,955
...l'm going to find out why!

1226
01:46:11,679 --> 01:46:13,192
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

1227
01:46:31,600 --> 01:46:33,079
Sonorus!

1228
01:46:37,159 --> 01:46:42,279
Earlier today. Professor Moody placed
the Triwizard Cup deep within the maze.

1229
01:46:42,439 --> 01:46:47,194
Only he knows its exact position.
Now. as Mr. Diggory...

1230
01:46:49,200 --> 01:46:50,918
...and Mr. Potter...

1231
01:46:52,720 --> 01:46:54,392
...are tied for first position...

1232
01:46:54,559 --> 01:46:58,518
...they will be the first to enter the maze.
followed by Mr. Krum...

1233
01:46:59,720 --> 01:47:03,030
-...and Miss Delacour.
-Come on! Krum! Krum! Krum!

1234
01:47:03,920 --> 01:47:06,832
The first person to touch the cup
will be the winner!

1235
01:47:10,999 --> 01:47:13,638
l've instructed the staff
to patrol the perimeter.

1236
01:47:13,800 --> 01:47:16,598
