these past few months. Wormtail.

1313
01:59:54,559 --> 01:59:56,789
Thank you. master.

1314
01:59:57,360 --> 01:59:59,032
Thank you.

1315
02:00:01,999 --> 02:00:04,274
-Such a handsome boy.
-Don't touch him!

1316
02:00:05,679 --> 02:00:07,112
Harry.

1317
02:00:07,280 --> 02:00:09,953
I'd almost forgotten you were here.

1318
02:00:10,120 --> 02:00:14,352
Standing on the bones
of my father. Yeah.

1319
02:00:14,520 --> 02:00:15,839
I'd introduce you...

1320
02:00:16,000 --> 02:00:20,118
...but word has it you're almost
as famous as me these days.

1321
02:00:22,679 --> 02:00:25,239
The boy who lived.

1322
02:00:25,400 --> 02:00:28,198
How lies have fed your legend. Harry.

1323
02:00:28,360 --> 02:00:32,194
Shall I reveal what really happened
that night 13 years ago?

1324
02:00:32,359 --> 02:00:36,875
Shall I divulge how
I truly lost my powers?

1325
02:00:37,040 --> 02:00:38,473
Yes. shall I?

1326
02:00:38,920 --> 02:00:40,194
It was love.

1327
02:00:40,360 --> 02:00:44,672
You see. when dear. sweet Lily Potter
gave her life for her only son...

1328
02:00:44,840 --> 02:00:47,308
...she provided the ultimate protection.

1329
02:00:47,719 --> 02:00:49,437
I could not touch him.

1330
02:00:50,600 --> 02:00:52,670
It was old magic.

1331
02:00:52,839 --> 02:00:54,989
Something I should have foreseen.

1332
02:00:55,160 --> 02:00:56,878
But no matter. no matter.

1333
02:00:57,039 --> 02:00:59,155
Things have changed.

1334
02:00:59,880 --> 02:01:03,236
I can touch you...

1335
02:01:03,840 --> 02:01:05,478
...now.

1336
02:01:13,320 --> 02:01:14,594
Yeah.

1337
02:01:20,679 --> 02:01:24,194
Astonishing what a few drops
of your blood will do. eh. Harry?

1338
02:01:25,360 --> 02:01:26,952
Pick up your wand. Potter.

1339
02:01:28,520 --> 02:01:30,636
I said. pick it up! Get up! Get up!

1340
02:01:32,199 --> 02:01:34,394
You've been taught how to duel.
I presume. yes?

1341
02:01:34,560 --> 02:01:36,869
First. we bow to each other.

1342
02:01:37,039 --> 02:01:39,348
Come on. now. Harry.
The niceties must be observed.

1343
02:01:39,520 --> 02:01:42,592
Dumbledore wouldn't want you
to forget your manners. would he?

1344
02:01:42,759 --> 02:01:44,033
I said. bow.

1345
02:01:45,799 --> 02:01:49,951
-That's better. And now....
-No.

1346
02:01:50,359 --> 02:01:52,156
Crucio !

1347
02:01:54,520 --> 02:01:56,192
Crucio !

1348
02:01:57,199 --> 02:01:59,076
Attaboy. Harry.

1349
02:01:59,239 --> 02:02:01,275
Your parents would be proud.

1350
02:02:01,560 --> 02:02:04,836
Especially your filthy Muggle mother.

1351
02:02:04,999 --> 02:02:06,512
Exp elliar--

1352
02:02:09,400 --> 02:02:11,709
I'm going to kill you. Harry Potter.

1353
02:02:11,879 --> 02:02:13,790
I'm going to destroy you.

1354
02:02:15,880 --> 02:02:21,238
After tonight. no one will ever again
question my powers.

1355
02:02:21,839 --> 02:02:24,307
After tonight. if they speak of you...

1356
02:02:24,479 --> 02:02:27,039
...they'll speak only of how you...

1357
02:02:27,320 --> 02:02:29,072
...begged for death.

1358
02:02:29,239 --> 02:02:32,834
And I. being a merciful Lord...

1359
02:02:33,360 --> 02:02:34,918
...obliged.

1360
02:02:35,239 --> 02:02:36,672
Get up!

1361
02:02:41,479 --> 02:02:43,356
Don't you turn your back on me.
Harry Potter!

1362
02:02:43,520 --> 02:02:45,670
I want you to look at me
when I kill you!

1363
02:02:45,839 --> 02:02:48,911
I want to see the light
leave your eyes!

1364
02:03:02,279 --> 02:03:03,951
Have it your way.

1365
02:03:04,959 --> 02:03:07,234
-Exp elliarm us!
-A vada Keda vra!

1366
02:03:24,040 --> 02:03:26,600
Do nothing! He's mine to finish!

1367
02:03:30,999 --> 02:03:32,637
He's mine!

1368
02:04:04,360 --> 02:04:08,194
Harry. when the connection is broken.
you must get to the Portkey.

1369
02:04:08,360 --> 02:04:10,316
We can linger for a moment
to give you some time...

1370
02:04:10,480 --> 02:04:12,198
...but only a moment.
Do you understand?

1371
02:04:13,320 --> 02:04:16,232
Harry. take my body back. will you?

1372
02:04:16,400 --> 02:04:18,834
Take my body back to my father.

1373
02:04:19,840 --> 02:04:21,114
Let go.

1374
02:04:21,559 --> 02:04:23,436
Sweetheart. you're ready.

1375
02:04:24,239 --> 02:04:26,753
Let go! Let go!

1376
02:04:32,279 --> 02:04:33,598
Accio!

1377
02:04:39,080 --> 02:04:40,991
No!

1378
02:04:53,200 --> 02:04:54,758
He did it!

1379
02:04:55,920 --> 02:04:57,512
Harry!

1380
02:05:00,199 --> 02:05:01,632
Harry!

1381
02:05:02,760 --> 02:05:05,877
No! No! No. don't!

1382
02:05:06,160 --> 02:05:07,957
For God's sake. Dumbledore.
what's happened?

1383
02:05:08,239 --> 02:05:10,707
He's back. He's back.

1384
02:05:10,880 --> 02:05:12,836
Voldemort's back.

1385
02:05:12,999 --> 02:05:15,274
Cedric. he asked me
to bring his body back.

1386
02:05:15,439 --> 02:05:17,669
I couldn't leave him. not there.

1387
02:05:17,840 --> 02:05:20,513
It's all right. Harry. It's all right.

1388
02:05:20,679 --> 02:05:22,909
He's home. You both are.

1389
02:05:23,079 --> 02:05:26,549
Keep everybody in their seats.
A boy has just been killed.

1390
02:05:29,480 --> 02:05:32,950
The body must be moved. Dumbledore.
There are too many people.

1391
02:05:33,280 --> 02:05:34,918
Let me through.

1392
02:05:35,079 --> 02:05:36,512
Let me through!

1393
02:05:38,359 --> 02:05:39,553
Let me through!

1394
02:05:39,719 --> 02:05:41,072
That's my son!

1395
02:05:42,320 --> 02:05:43,719
That's my boy!

1396
02:05:46,439 --> 02:05:49,033
It's my boy!

1397
02:05:51,719 --> 02:05:55,155
-Come on. Get up. Easy. easy!
-No.

1398
02:05:55,319 --> 02:05:58,152
This is not where you want to be
right now. Come on.

1399
02:05:58,799 --> 02:06:00,915
No!

1400
02:06:03,879 --> 02:06:06,154
It's all right. I got you.

1401
02:06:06,320 --> 02:06:09,517
I got you. Come on. Easy. now.

1402
02:06:13,360 --> 02:06:15,078
No!

1403
02:06:16,160 --> 02:06:17,957
No!

1404
02:06:58,599 --> 02:07:00,237
Are you all right. Potter?

1405
02:07:00,800 --> 02:07:02,631
Does it hurt? That?

1406
02:07:02,800 --> 02:07:04,518
Not so much now.

1407
02:07:05,440 --> 02:07:07,431
Perhaps I'd better take a look at it.

1408
02:07:10,439 --> 02:07:12,350
The cup was a Portkey.

1409
02:07:14,960 --> 02:07:16,712
Someone had bewitched it.

1410
02:07:16,999 --> 02:07:18,990
What was it like?

1411
02:07:19,319 --> 02:07:20,911
-What was he like?
-Who?

1412
02:07:21,080 --> 02:07:22,752
The Dark Lord.

1413
02:07:24,999 --> 02:07:27,957
What was it like
to stand in his presence?

1414
02:07:29,160 --> 02:07:30,912
I don't know.

1415
02:07:33,639 --> 02:07:36,437
It was like I'd fallen
into one of my dreams...

1416
02:07:39,280 --> 02:07:41,191
...into one of my nightmares.

1417
02:07:59,160 --> 02:08:00,673
Were there others?

1418
02:08:00,839 --> 02:08:02,989
In the graveyard. were there others?

1419
02:08:06,759 --> 02:08:08,112


1420
02:08:08,800 --> 02:08:12,554
I don't think I said anything
about a graveyard. professor.

1421
02:08:19,720 --> 02:08:22,837
“Marvelous creatures. dragons.
aren't they?“

1422
02:08:27,080 --> 02:08:29,992
Did you think that miserable oaf
would've led you into the woods...

1423
02:08:30,160 --> 02:08:31,991
...if I hadn't suggested it?

1424
02:08:35,399 --> 02:08:38,914
Do you think Cedric Diggory would've
told you to open the egg underwater...

1425
02:08:39,080 --> 02:08:41,469
...if I hadn't told him first myself?

1426
02:08:43,040 --> 02:08:45,600
Did you think Neville Longbottom.
the witless wonder...

1427
02:08:45,759 --> 02:08:48,831
...could've provided you with gillyweed
if I hadn't given him the book...

1428
02:08:48,999 --> 02:08:50,478
...that led him straight to it?

1429
02:08:58,560 --> 02:09:02,394
It was you from the beginning.
You put my name in the Goblet of Fire.

1430
02:09:02,920 --> 02:09:06,435
-You bewitched Krum. but you--
-“But-- But--“

1431
02:09:06,599 --> 02:09:08,669
You won because I made it so. Potter.

1432
02:09:09,280 --> 02:09:12,636
You ended up in that graveyard tonight
because it was meant to be so.

1433
02:09:12,800 --> 02:09:14,028
And now the deed is done.

1434
02:09:15,639 --> 02:09:19,791
The blood that runs through these veins
runs within the Dark Lord.

1435
02:09:27,960 --> 02:09:31,316
Imagine how he will reward me
when he learns...

1436
02:09:32,199 --> 02:09:34,588
...that I have once and for all...

1437
02:09:35,200 --> 02:09:39,352
...silenced the great Harry Potter.

1438
02:09:39,519 --> 02:09:40,713
Exp elliarm us!

1439
02:09:45,240 --> 02:09:46,434
Severus.

1440
02:09:48,839 --> 02:09:50,272
That's it. take it.

1441
02:09:52,160 --> 02:09:55,470
-Do you know who I am?
-A|bus Dumbledore.

1442
02:09:55,640 --> 02:09:58,234
-Are you Alastor Moody? Are you?
-No.

1443
02:09:58,400 --> 02:10:01,358
Is he in this room? Is he in this room?

1444
02:10:04,279 --> 02:10:05,758
Harry. away from there!

1445
02:10:25,880 --> 02:10:29,077
-You all right. Alastor?
-|'m sorry. Albus.

1446
02:10:29,999 --> 02:10:31,990
That's Moody. But then who's--?

1447
02:10:33,719 --> 02:10:34,754
Polyjuice Potion.

1448
02:10:34,919 --> 02:10:38,036
Now we know who's been stealing
from your stores. Severus.

1449
02:10:38,279 --> 02:10:40,110
We'll get you up in a minute.

1450
02:11:13,159 --> 02:11:14,478
Harry!

1451
02:11:17,999 --> 02:11:20,115
Barty Crouch Junior.

1452
02:11:20,359 --> 02:11:23,157
I'll show you mine
if you show me yours.

1453
02:11:25,439 --> 02:11:26,588
Your arm. Harry.

1454
02:11:30,759 --> 02:11:32,909
You know what this means. don't you?

1455
02:11:33,799 --> 02:11:35,073
He's back.

1456
02:11:36,199 --> 02:11:38,269
Lord Voldemort has returned.

1457
02:11:39,160 --> 02:11:41,390
I'm sorry. sir. I couldn't help it.

1458
02:11:41,600 --> 02:11:45,957
Send an ow! to Azkaban. I think
they'll find they're missing a prisoner.

1459
02:11:46,400 --> 02:11:48,789
-|'|| be welcomed back like a hero.
-Perhaps.

1460
02:11:49,319 --> 02:11:52,072
Personally. I've never had much time
for heroes.

1461
02:12:11,159 --> 02:12:13,719
Today. we acknowledge...

1462
02:12:14,400 --> 02:12:17,039
...a really terrible loss.

1463
02:12:19,079 --> 02:12:21,718
Cedric Diggory was. as you all know...

1464
02:12:21,879 --> 02:12:24,109
...exceptionally hard-working...

1465
02:12:25,040 --> 02:12:27,235
...infinitely fair-minded...

1466
02:12:27,799 --> 02:12:29,994
...and. most importantly...

1467
02:12:30,279 --> 02:12:34,670
...a fierce. fierce friend.

1468
02:12:35,760 --> 02:12:39,958
Now. I think. therefore. you have
the right to know exactly how he died.

1469
02:12:42,880 --> 02:12:44,359
You see...

1470
02:12:45,160 --> 02:12:47,151
...Cedric Diggory was murdered...

1471
02:12:48,039 --> 02:12:49,950
...by Lord Voldemort!

1472
02:12:51,759 --> 02:12:55,195
The Ministry of Magic
does not wish me to tell you this.

1473
02:12:55,800 --> 02:12:59,349
But not to do so. I think.
would be an insult to his memory.

1474
02:13:01,439 --> 02:13:03,031
Now. the pain...

1475
02:13:03,200 --> 02:13:06,715
...we all feel at this dreadful loss
reminds me...

1476
02:13:06,880 --> 02:13:08,154
...and reminds us...

1477
02:13:08,320 --> 02:13:11,869
...that while we may come from different
places and speak in different tongues...

1478
02:13:12,039 --> 02:13:15,315
...our hearts beat as one.

1479
02:13:15,799 --> 02:13:17,755
In light of recent events...

1480
02:13:18,080 --> 02:13:22,790
...the bonds of friendship we've made
this year will be more important than ever.

1481
02:13:23,639 --> 02:13:28,759
Remember that. and Cedric Diggory
will not have died in vain.

1482
02:13:29,159 --> 02:13:31,229
You remember that...

1483
02:13:31,800 --> 02:13:34,712
...and we'll celebrate a boy who was...

1484
02:13:35,239 --> 02:13:37,594
...kind and honest...

1485
02:13:38,080 --> 02:13:42,471
...and brave and true.
right to the very end.

1486
02:14:06,680 --> 02:14:08,636
I never liked these curtains.

1487
02:14:09,200 --> 02:14:11,760
Set them on fire in my fourth year.

1488
02:14:12,080 --> 02:14:13,832
